Maven follows the "convention over configuration" principle.
It defines a standard directory layout and a lifecycle (compile â†’ test â†’ package â†’ install â†’ deploy).

You declare your project configuration and dependencies in a single file: pom.xml.
Maven handles dependency management automatically from the Maven Central Repository.

